&quot;He never knew who it was,&quot; he says.
The victim, according to José, did not close the account.
&quot;It just put privacy on it.&quot;
It then explains a series of steps to configure the account safely.
Unlike Jorge, this guy would upload photos of acquaintances in awkward or embarrassing situations.
Yes, I would, if I don&#39;t like him or I want him.
&quot;Although I know that this is cyberbullying,&quot; he says.
Key questions
Marielos Porras, an English teacher with a degree in Education and Learning, believes that in order to guide children and adolescents, it must be understood that the purpose of social networks is to inform.
&quot;Internet emerged as a means to search for information, but with the appearance of these sites the rules of the game changed,&quot; he says.
Porras points out that the academic Marc Prensky, master&#39;s degree in Pedagogy from Yale University and author of the work Nativos e Inmigrantes Digitales, coined these terms to explain the phenomenon.
The digital natives are they, the children and young people who were born with technology.
&quot;We are the digital immigrants that we have to teach them, when we are still learning,&quot; he says.
