Some think they are going to die and do not want to know anything.
&quot;If I&#39;m going to die, I&#39;d better burst three times a week,&quot; they say not in my case.
The change was for the better, I eat well, I exercise, I take medications.
To date, his parents only know that he suffered from cancer.
I live a normal life, like anyone else.
&quot;I work, I have many activities, I travel, I have an active sexual life, but co-responsible, I take care of myself and the other person&quot;, listed Fabrizio, who agreed to share his intimacy with MILENIO JALISCO to motivate with his testimony those who today, in the framework of World AIDS Day, they are afraid.
That they get tested, if they were at risk, that the sooner they know if they are HIV positive, the better and if they already have the diagnosis, that they learn that they can live like anyone else, being responsible.
That, his message, sums up the slogan of the battle against AIDS this 2012.
